text: Bede McCauley (11 June 1911 - 14 October 1994) was an Australian cricketer. He played four first-class matches for New South Wales between 1937/38 and 1938/39. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1911 births Category:1994 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers Category:Cricketers from Sydney
